name: Compute Definition
description: >
  Reusable compute logic for Conversation/Compute steps.

  A Compute Definition may contain named constants and named functions. A
  Conversation/Compute step can reference the definition and select an entry
  function.

  This type intentionally does not strongly type BEX functions or operators.
  BEX syntax and execution semantics are defined by the Compute processor and
  BEX specification, not by repo.blue field-level schemas in this version.

constants:
  type: Dictionary
  description: >
    Named constants available through `$const`. Keys are constant names; values
    are arbitrary Blue values.

functions:
  type: Dictionary
  description: >
    Named reusable BEX functions. Keys are function names; values are function
    definitions.